headline: 3 Top Dividend Stocks to Buy in 2025 With $200
summary: If you have a few hundred dollars that you don't need for reducing debt or covering other living expenses, there are solid companies offering tempting dividend yields right now.  Realty Income (NYSE: O), Target (NYSE: TGT), and Philip Morris International (NYSE: PM) have dividend yields that are well above the S&P 500 average of 1.24%.  Jennifer Saibil (Realty Income): Realty Income is one of the best dividend stocks to own at any time, but 2025 could be an important year for the real estate industry in general, and Realty Income's business could be even stronger than usual.
